9. Overfitting

Overfitting occurs when:

model memorizes training data,
but performs poorly on unseen data.

Goal of ML:

Generalization

not memorization.

10. Famous Principle

“All models are wrong, but some are useful.”

Meaning:

models are approximations,
useful models capture important patterns.
