Final Summary

The lecture explains that:

Machine learning starts with function approximation.
Data is used to estimate unknown relationships.
Complex real-world problems cannot be modeled deterministically.
Therefore, modern ML relies heavily on probability and statistics.
Modern AI systems are fundamentally probabilistic models.
